13
00:01:41,37 --> 00:01:45,87
我叫做罗杰布朗 我只有168公分高
My name is Roger Brown. I am 1.68 m.

14
00:01:45,87 --> 00:01:50,58
说我心里不平衡吧，要做些补偿
You do not need a psychologist to understand that it must be compensated.

15
00:01:51,50 --> 00:01:55,33
例如，我挑高天花板的房子：三千万 （1.5亿台币）
My house, for example. Ceiling: 30 million.

16
00:01:55,33 --> 00:02:00,66
我不喜欢，也买不起 但是她... 她喜欢
I do not like it, and can't afford it. But she loves it.

17
00:02:00,66 --> 00:02:03,87
你有很多像我一样要开画廊的朋友？
How often do you have a girlfriend who opens a gallery?

18
00:02:03,87 --> 00:02:11,24
我都跟别人说这是遗产 其实我继承的东西是别的
I said it was an inheritance. Something I had to say. But I have just inherited bad genes.

19
00:02:11,25 --> 00:02:15,16
‘神探专访’ <i>要发觉真相，是一个繁琐的过程</i>
It has been a tedious process to find out the truth.

20
00:02:15,33 --> 00:02:19,58
像我这样的人如果说还缺什么，也只有一样：
If like me someone wants to get what he wants, there is only one thing:

21
00:02:19,58 --> 00:02:24,83
钱 很多很多的钱
Money. A lot of money.

22
00:02:30,25 --> 00:02:35,29
可是戴安娜认为 还有一样比什么都重要
But there is one thing Diana wants more than anything else.

23
00:02:35,29 --> 00:02:41,37
而那却是我唯一不想给她的东西
And that's just the thing I do not want to give her.

24
00:02:41,54 --> 00:02:46,29
- 她是不是很可爱？ - 非常可爱
- Isn't she cute? - Very cute.

25
00:02:48,29 --> 00:02:53,45
我的妻子戴安娜是最美丽的人，高挑又聪明
Diana Strm-Eliassen is on of the most beautiful, tall, smart.

26
00:02:53,62 --> 00:02:58,83
她在这个世界上 想要什么都能得到
On of those accustomed to love. Those who take it for granted.

27
00:02:59,00 --> 00:03:03,41
很多男人都会愿意为她付出 尤其那些身高超过 168的人
And lots of men want to give her that. Men who are taller than 1.68.

28
00:03:08,54 --> 00:03:14,16
然而是我追求到她 因为我会把握机会
But soon it's my turn. My opportunity. I can feel it.

29
00:03:14,33 --> 00:03:21,45
于此同时，我也去玩 因为不能放松玩乐的人，不会成功
In the meantime, I play loud. For he who does not play, will not win.

30
00:03:24,00 --> 00:03:26,62
- 你明天要做什么？ - 问这要干嘛？
- What are you doing tomorrow? - Why do you ask?

31
00:03:26,79 --> 00:03:31,95
有人请我们去吃饭
We are invited to dinner.

32
00:03:33,62 --> 00:03:36,79
- 有人请我们去吃饭？ - 是啊
- We are invited to dinner? - Yes.

33
00:03:36,95 --> 00:03:40,91
- 你跟别人说我们的事？ - 只有一个，我想介绍你们认识
- Are you talking about us with others? - There is one I want you to meet.

34
00:03:41,08 --> 00:03:45,99
我们玩完了 我很抱歉
This ends now. I really am sorry.

35
00:03:46,00 --> 00:03:49,20
- 我只是想... - 不行 罗悌 ...
- Let me be ... - No. Lotte ...

36
00:03:49,20 --> 00:03:52,99
- 我们之间没什么 - 我们之间没什么？
- There is no us. - Isn't there?

37
00:04:03,50 --> 00:04:06,70
- 一个令人印象深刻的履历，兰德 - 谢谢您！
- An impressive resume, Lander. - Thank you.

38
00:04:06,70 --> 00:04:10,95
事实上，我觉得我就是‘探路者’要找的人
Yes, I think I am the right man for Pathfinder.

39
00:04:10,95 --> 00:04:16,37
- 你的休闲时间都做些什么？ - 我哪来的时间休息啊
- What do you do in your spare time? - Is there such a thing?

40
00:04:17,25 --> 00:04:21,49
你住在奥斯陆 妻子叫做...？
You live in Oslo. In Skyen. And you're married to ...?

41
00:04:21,50 --> 00:04:24,91
卡蜜拉  结婚9年了 有两个孩子 都还在上学
Camilla. Been married for nine years. Two children. They go to school.

42
00:04:25,12 --> 00:04:29,62
- 她也上班？ - 是的 在市中心的律师事务所
- She working? - Yes. In a law office in the center.

43
00:04:29,79 --> 00:04:32,99
- 如果孩子生病在家谁顾？ - 她会顾
- Who is at home if a child is sick? - She is.

44
00:04:33,00 --> 00:04:35,29
- 没请佣人？ - 没有
- No domestic help? - No.

45
00:04:35,29 --> 00:04:36,91
- 有养狗？ - 没有
- Dog? - No.

46
00:04:36,91 --> 00:04:39,87
- 会过敏？ - 不会
- Allergies? - No.

47
00:04:51,87 --> 00:04:54,95
作为一个领导者 您的声誉如何？
What is your reputation as a leader worth?

48
00:04:55,12 --> 00:04:57,99
我的声誉？是什??么意思？
My reputation? What do you mean?

49
00:04:59,25 --> 00:05:02,95
那些画是朱利安?奥贝的作品 市值25万 （125万台币）
The plant was founded by Julian Opie. Worth a quarter of a million.

50
00:05:02,95 --> 00:05:06,16
- 你有收藏这种价位的艺术品吗？ - 事实上，我有
- Do you own art in the price range? - Yes, actually.

51
00:05:06,16 --> 00:05:09,87
一幅蒙克的版画 ‘胸针’
A lithograph by Munch. A brooch.

52
00:05:09,87 --> 00:05:13,91
你知道如何监赏艺品的价值吗？
Can you see what it's worth just by looking at it?

53
00:05:14,08 --> 00:05:18,58
那只是一些简单着色，单调的圆形和线条
This consists of circles and lines. Monotone coloring, without texture.

54
00:05:18,58 --> 00:05:25,20
之所以价值 25万，是艺术家的名字
The thing that makes it worth a quarter of a million, is the artist's name.

55
00:05:25,37 --> 00:05:29,08
- 这道理同样适用于领导者？ - 正是如此
- And the same goes for leaders? - Exactly.

56
00:05:31,87 --> 00:05:36,33
这就是你无法得到这份工作的原因
And that is why you will not get this job.

57
00:05:36,33 --> 00:05:42,83
- 什么？ - 天哪，你不该只身前来
- What? - Oh my God, you arranged it yourself.

58
00:05:43,87 --> 00:05:48,74
- 我该怎么做呢？ - 必须由别人来介绍你这个人
- What else could I do? - Made someone to tell us about you.

59
00:05:48,75 --> 00:05:52,33
听起来你没有体会我的意思，也许是联系得不够
Sounded like you were not aware of it when we contacted you.

60
00:05:52,50 --> 00:05:56,20
要把它弄成一场秀，兰德 听着 ...
Everything is a game, Lander. Listen now ...

61
00:05:56,20 --> 00:06:00,04
探路者的董事长和财务经理，明天都会来
Pathfinders Chairman and financial manager will come tomorrow.

62
00:06:00,04 --> 00:06:03,29
我希望你们碰个面 礼貌上的
I want you to meet them. Listen politely.

63
00:06:03,45 --> 00:06:06,54
你要表现得其实你不在意这个职位
How do you explain why you are no longer interested.

64
00:06:07,91 --> 00:06:12,16
- 他们会觉得我很虚假 - 不. 你要野心勃勃
- They will perceive me as unserious. - No. As ambitious.

65
00:06:12,16 --> 00:06:15,24
要表现的你清楚自己的价值
As someone who knows his own value.

66
00:06:17,08 --> 00:06:22,79
- 兰德，这是你的机会 - 机会？
- Lander, this is your opportunity. - Possibility?

67
00:06:22,79 --> 00:06:25,87
让我来帮你建立声誉
Let me build your reputation.

68
00:06:26,91 --> 00:06:32,33
我保证你在两年内 就会找到五倍于现有收入的工作
I will promise you a job with five times your salary in two years.

69
00:06:32,50 --> 00:06:35,37
你要怎么保证？
How can you promise that?

70
00:06:35,37 --> 00:06:42,08
因为我从来没有给过客户，任何没有价值的意见
Because I have never given a customer a recommendation that he has not followed.

71
00:06:42,08 --> 00:06:45,54
- 要怎么做呢？ - ‘作者的名字’
- But how? - The answer begins with "R".

72
00:06:46,20 --> 00:06:50,33
- 声誉... - 会帮助你推展整个事业
- Reputation ... - The whole career is based on it.

73
00:06:52,41 --> 00:06:55,49
你好
Hello.

74
00:06:56,04 --> 00:07:01,83
您跟那位耶利米兰德以及‘探路者’ 明天12点开会
You have an interview with Jeremiah Lander and Pathfinder tomorrow at 12.

75
00:07:01,83 --> 00:07:05,45
- 文件里有细节 - 是的 好
- The information is in the file. - Yes. Good.

76
00:07:05,45 --> 00:07:10,54
你妻子的画廊这个周末开幕，我在想...
Your wife's supposed to open a gallery this weekend, and I was wondering ...

77
00:07:10,54 --> 00:07:14,58
- 我是否能去呢？ - 你有被邀请吗？
- Is it possible to go there? - Are you invited?

78
00:07:14,58 --> 00:07:17,87
- 我有，我能去吗？ - 你说呢？
- Yes, do I do it? - Will you?

79
00:07:17,87 --> 00:07:23,16
我收到了卡斯帕汉森街 整修费 35万7千元的发票 （台币180万）
I have received an invoice for 357 000 for renovations in Kasper Hansen Street.

80
00:07:23,16 --> 00:07:29,70
对 我帮戴安娜出的钱 她周五画廊要开幕
Right. I have helped Diana with expenses. She opens the gallery on Friday.

81
00:07:29,70 --> 00:07:34,99
你该削减开支了，你现在随时会破产
You need to cut down on spending. You can go bankrupt at any time.

82
00:07:35,00 --> 00:07:37,37
我会搞定的
I'm working on it.

83
00:07:37,37 --> 00:07:41,08
我必须告诉你的情况是多么严重
I must tell you how serious the situation is.

84
00:07:41,08 --> 00:07:44,70
你已经透支了几十万的卡...
You have overdrawn the card with several hundred thousand ...

85
00:07:44,70 --> 00:07:48,66
我要接另一通电话 晚点打给你
I have another phone call here. I'll call you later.

86
00:07:48,66 --> 00:07:55,20
有一个新目标 叫耶利米兰德，住在奥斯陆
You have a candidate. Jeremiah Lander, lives in Skyen.

87
00:07:56,41 --> 00:08:01,58
- 没错 是我们公司的 什么时候？ - 明天12点在阿尔法开会
- Yes. We have him. When? - A meeting at the Alfa tomorrow at 12.

88
00:08:01,58 --> 00:08:04,91
- 家中无人？ - 没有 他的妻子在市区工作
- No one home? - No. His wife works in the city.

89
00:08:04,91 --> 00:08:08,24
我们二十分后见
We meet about twenty.

90
00:08:35,91 --> 00:08:38,24
‘的黎波里’保全公司

91
00:09:37,00 --> 00:09:40,62
哥德堡收赃物的人，要抽百分之五十
The fence in Gothenburg would get fifty percent.

92
00:09:40,62 --> 00:09:44,45
他 奥雅纳 将获得 20％，负责关闭保全警铃
Ove Kjikerud would get 20% for disabling the alarm, get the art -

93
00:09:44,45 --> 00:09:47,04
还有将艺品带到瑞典
- and run to Sweden with it.

94
00:09:47,04 --> 00:09:50,62
请到在‘的黎波里’保全上班的他 可能是我做过的最明智的事情之一
To hire him in Tripoli was probably one of the smartest things I had done.

95
00:09:50,62 --> 00:09:54,91
虽然这样我只能分到八万  八万！ （40万台币）
Although I was left with 80 000. 80 000!

96
00:09:54,91 --> 00:09:59,16
它甚至还不够付下一季的房贷
It was not even for the next quarterly installment of the house.

97
00:09:59,16 --> 00:10:02,24
必须另外再想办法
Something must be done.

98
00:10:06,12 --> 00:10:10,24
您好！感谢你们的到来
Hello. Thank you for coming.

99
00:10:22,29 --> 00:10:26,12
- 好盛大的场合 - 还有一半的客人还没来勒
- It does look very good. - Half of them have not arrived yet.

100
00:10:26,12 --> 00:10:32,29
- 我有好多人要招呼 ... - 嘿，一切都会顺利的
- But I do not have to meet ... - Hey, it will go very well.

101
00:10:32,29 --> 00:10:35,08
- 恭喜 刚的表演太棒了 - 谢谢您！
- Congratulations. Fantastic show. - Thank you.

102
00:10:35,08 --> 00:10:38,70
真是疯狂的一天 我现在还不能放松
This has been a wild day. I can not tell it now.

103
00:10:38,70 --> 00:10:42,41
- 有个人介绍给你认识 - 是谁？
- But I want you to meet him. - Meet with whom?

104
00:10:59,95 --> 00:11:03,74
- 这是我的丈夫 罗杰布朗 - 我叫柯乐斯 格雷夫
- This is my husband. Roger Brown. - Clas Greve.

105
00:11:03,91 --> 00:11:08,54
柯乐斯刚从荷兰 搬来挪威
Clas has just moved here. From the Netherlands.

106
00:11:08,54 --> 00:11:15,66
你好，你要去吗？不，孩子们会很高兴的
Hello, are you going? No, the kids just cheer up.

107
00:11:16,75 --> 00:11:21,08
- 来挪威是为了什么？工作？ - 我来继承我祖母的公寓
- What brings you to Norway? Work? - I inherited my grandmother's apartment.

108
00:11:21,25 --> 00:11:23,62
- 她是挪威人？ - 没错
- She was Norwegian? - Yes.

109
00:11:23,62 --> 00:11:29,12
我提前退休 所以要装修公寓
I retired early. I'm going to renovate the apartment.

110
00:11:29,12 --> 00:11:31,83
退休？哪一行？
Retired? From what?

111
00:11:31,83 --> 00:11:35,04
我是一家荷兰科技企业的董事
I was a director of a Dutch technology enterprise.

112
00:11:35,04 --> 00:11:39,49
主要从事 GPS 全球定位系统...我们...
We worked mainly with GPS. Shall we ...?

113
00:11:39,50 --> 00:11:43,49
- 荷兰的？该不会是‘贺得’吧？ - 是的，没错
- Dutch? Not Hote, right? - Yes, exactly.

114
00:11:43,50 --> 00:11:48,79
他不是才刚要被一家美国大公司收购了？ 谷津科技 ？
Were not they just bought up by a large American company? Amtech?

115
00:11:48,79 --> 00:11:52,66
- 您也是同行吗？ - 不是
- You work yourself in the industry? - No.

116
00:11:52,66 --> 00:11:56,20
- 你为什么离开？ - 我谈公事烦你不好吧
- Why did you leave? - Let me not bore you with work talk.

117
00:11:56,20 --> 00:12:02,33
我在招聘领域工作 已经习惯了这类谈话
I work in the recruitment industry. You do not bore me out with work talk.

118
00:12:02,33 --> 00:12:05,12
- 你知道‘探路者’吗？ - 当然 是我们的竞争对手
- Do you know Pathfinder? - Of course. Our competitors.

119
00:12:05,12 --> 00:12:08,04
小而美的公司
Small. Skilled.

120
00:12:08,04 --> 00:12:12,29
我该走了... 祝您晚安
I must go. Have a good evening.

121
00:12:12,29 --> 00:12:15,66
柯乐斯 ...探路者在找一个新的经理人
Clas ... Pathfinder seeks a new boss.

122
00:12:15,83 --> 00:12:19,20
一个能抵御国外收购企图的人
One that can withstand takeover attempts from abroad.

123
00:12:19,20 --> 00:12:21,87
- 要不要来一起开个会？ - 抱歉 我...
- Shall we have a meeting? - Sorry.

124
00:12:21,87 --> 00:12:26,29
周一12点一起午餐 我们也可以谈谈别的事
A lunch. Monday at 12. We can talk about something else.

125
00:12:26,29 --> 00:12:29,49
艺术，装修，请外籍工人...
Arts, renovation, Polish workers ...

126
00:12:29,50 --> 00:12:32,49
我写餐厅的名字给你 好地方
I will write down the name of a good restaurant.

127
00:12:32,50 --> 00:12:35,99
我好像恭敬不如从命
You do not take no for an answer?

128
00:12:37,45 --> 00:12:41,49
公司给你的退休临别礼物？
A parting gift for a long and faithful service?

129
00:12:41,50 --> 00:12:45,08
不，是我偷拿的
No, I stole it.

130
00:12:46,66 --> 00:12:51,62
到时后见 向你迷人的妻子问候
When we meet. Say hello to your charming wife.

131
00:13:02,08 --> 00:13:06,66
- 这是我的丈夫 - 罗杰布朗
- This is my husband. - Roger Brown.

132
00:13:06,66 --> 00:13:09,99
- 我是布雷德，刑事调查局 - 电视上的神探本人
- Brede Sperre, Criminal Investigation Department - You have been on TV.

133
00:13:10,00 --> 00:13:13,62
- 他在调查艺术品盗窃案 - 不是凶杀案？
- He investigates art thefts. - Not murder?

134
00:13:13,83 --> 00:13:18,16
我们正全力调查本案 我一定要抓到他
We employ all resources on this. We must stop it.

135
00:13:18,33 --> 00:13:22,74
- 你也在艺术产业？ - 不，我在一家猎头公司工作
- Are you in the art industry? - No. I work as a headhunter.

136
00:13:22,75 --> 00:13:27,74
- 是人力仲介业 ‘阿尔法’ - 你是那家公司的股东之一
- In the recruitment industry. Alfa. - One of the partners, that is.

137
00:13:27,91 --> 00:13:31,54
我刚刚正在称赞你妻子的美丽耳环
I gave your wife a compliment for those exclusive earrings.

138
00:13:31,54 --> 00:13:35,62
- 她说，是你送的礼物 - 没错
- She said they were a gift from you. - Yes.

139
00:13:36,16 --> 00:13:41,33
是的，我们公司的分红机制不错
Yes, the best of us good bonus schemes.

